  "text": "The next lemma is well known. For the convenience of the reader we shall sketch a proof since the result is employed in the proof of Theorem 4.3. Remark 7.7: In the proof of Theorem 2.2 we could have worked with the Hopf algebroid (KU * (CP ∞ ), KU * KU ⊗ KU * KU * (CP ∞ )) by restricting the comodule structure and using (ungraded) Landweber exactness. In this way one can bootstrap a proof of Theorem 2.2 more directly from [CITATION_1] by using base change isomorphisms with no mention of graded Hopf algebroids. In the same spirit, we note there is an isomorphism KGL τ * (X ) ∼ = KGL * (X τ ) ⊗ KU * (CP ∞ ) KU * .",
